# Convolios — Project Context

## What is this?
Convolios is a desktop app (Tauri 2 + React) that merges all messaging channels into one AI-enriched inbox, organized by Person, not by App.

## Read first
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — full technical reference: data flows, schema, Tauri commands, Edge Functions, known issues.
- `PLAN.md` — master plan with vision, channel support, build progress, and tech debt.
- `README.md` — product overview, project structure, and setup instructions.

## Stack (actual, as of April 2026)
- **Shell:** Tauri 2 (Rust + React)
- **Frontend:** React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 (custom UI, no component library)
- **State:** Zustand + @tauri-store/zustand (persistent)
- **Data fetching:** React Query v5 + LocalStorage persistence
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (OTP magic link) — originally Clerk, pivoted
- **DB:** Supabase (Postgres + pgvector + Realtime)
- **Messaging API:** Unipile (direct REST from Rust, no SDK)
- **AI:** Gemini 2.5 Flash (triage on ingest) + Gemini Embedding 2 (planned, not yet active)
- **Deep linking:** tauri-plugin-deep-link (`convolios://auth`)

## Current phase
**Phase 3 — Core UI (mostly complete).** Inbox, thread view, compose, settings all functional. Triage classification and filtering working. Semantic search, context briefs, and reply drafting not started.

## Secrets
All secrets are in 1Password vault `P&Co — Convolios`. Use `op read` or `op inject` to access. NEVER hardcode secrets. Use `.env.local` (gitignored).

## Key decisions
- **Single-user app** — always one user, never multi-tenant. Mobile app may come later but syncs the same account.
- Dark mode first, Discord-inspired dark aesthetic
- Never auto-send messages (ban risk) — AI drafts, human confirms
- Unipile is the sole messaging provider (no ChannelProvider abstraction yet)
- All Unipile calls go through the Rust backend (not the frontend)
- Webhooks are processed by Supabase Edge Functions (Deno)
- Realtime updates via Supabase Realtime + fallback polling

## Known issues
- Embedding column is vector(2000) but Gemini outputs 3072-dim (irrelevant until embedding pipeline is built)
- Base64 avatars stored in persons.avatar_url (works, bloats rows)

